WEBVTT

00:15.598 --> 00:16.933
Hey.

00:16.933 --> 00:17.642
Hey, Russell.

00:17.642 --> 00:19.436
Sorry I'm late.
I had a thing.

00:19.436 --> 00:20.270
Yeah, I figured.

00:20.270 --> 00:21.896
I ordered you
a burger.

00:21.896 --> 00:22.939
Oh, you ordered for me?

00:22.939 --> 00:24.857
Great. Why don't
we just make out?

00:24.857 --> 00:28.695
Because I don't know
where you've been.

00:29.112 --> 00:31.656
But I've got some news.

00:31.656 --> 00:33.491
I moved in with Jennifer.

00:33.491 --> 00:35.618
Why? When you
lost your sublet,

00:35.618 --> 00:37.370
I said you could
stay on my couch.

00:37.370 --> 00:39.456
Might wanna flip
the cushions first.

00:39.456 --> 00:42.459
Yeah, this thing with
Jennifer isn't temporary,

00:42.459 --> 00:46.088
because last night,
I proposed to her.

00:46.088 --> 00:48.005
It gets worse!

00:48.005 --> 00:50.758
What are you, the dumbest
idiot in the world?

00:50.758 --> 00:52.344
Thanks for sharing
my happiness.

00:52.344 --> 00:54.054
You've only known
her seven months.

00:54.054 --> 00:56.473
You know what-- make
sure the baby's yours.

00:56.473 --> 00:58.391
Make her take
a paternity test.

00:58.391 --> 01:00.518
She's not pregnant.

01:00.518 --> 01:02.604
Oh, shootin' blanks?

01:02.604 --> 01:06.358
No, no, I proposed
because I love her.

01:06.358 --> 01:08.651
That's so gay.

01:08.651 --> 01:10.987
Being in love
with a woman is gay.

01:10.987 --> 01:14.449
No, but saying it
out loud to another guy is.

01:14.449 --> 01:17.744
Look, there's no wedding date,
no plans, no pressure.

01:17.744 --> 01:19.787
I didn't even get her
a ring yet, man.

01:19.787 --> 01:21.248
I've got the best
of all worlds.

01:21.248 --> 01:23.375
There's only one world,
and I have the best of it.

01:23.375 --> 01:25.001
I do what I want,
I date who I want,

01:25.001 --> 01:28.838
and I sleep with
whoever will let me.

01:28.838 --> 01:30.965
Look, I've had all that.

01:30.965 --> 01:32.759
Okay, now I'm done.

01:32.759 --> 01:33.718
Jennifer's the one.

01:33.718 --> 01:35.720
I think you're
making a huge mistake.

01:35.720 --> 01:37.347
Lockin' it down
with one chick

01:37.347 --> 01:38.931
is a horrible, horrible--
Hey!

01:38.931 --> 01:41.309
There's Little
Miss Sunshine.

01:41.309 --> 01:42.394
Hey, guys.

01:42.394 --> 01:45.355
Mwah. So did he tell you
he proposed?

01:45.355 --> 01:46.981
Yeah, he did.

01:46.981 --> 01:50.026
Oh, uh, hooray!

01:50.026 --> 01:51.861
It's great news.

01:53.738 --> 01:57.742
♪♪ How many ways
to say I love you ♪♪

01:58.535 --> 02:03.831
♪♪ How many ways
to say that
I'm not scared ♪♪

02:03.831 --> 02:06.668
♪♪ With you by my side ♪♪

02:06.668 --> 02:09.129
♪♪ There is no denyin' ♪♪

02:09.129 --> 02:13.258
♪♪ I can't wait
for me and you ♪♪

02:16.136 --> 02:17.804
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

02:19.556 --> 02:20.097
Hey, Jeff.

02:20.097 --> 02:22.392
Audrey, did you
write a check?

02:22.392 --> 02:23.560
Yeah, I did.

02:23.560 --> 02:26.646
Well, you didn't
put it in the thing.

02:27.564 --> 02:30.192
Now it's all...

02:34.111 --> 02:35.447
Whatever.

02:35.905 --> 02:39.116
It was for the exterminator
that was here last week.

02:39.116 --> 02:40.577
It was, like, $60-ish...

02:40.577 --> 02:41.369
Sixty-ish.

02:41.369 --> 02:45.165
Well, great. Now we'll
just put that in here.

02:45.998 --> 02:50.253
There, now the checkbook
is totally balanced-ish.

02:50.253 --> 02:53.506
[LAUGHING]
You and that checkbook.

02:53.506 --> 02:54.382
Hey, look, we got invited

02:54.382 --> 02:57.427
to a really cool art opening
on Saturday night.

02:57.427 --> 02:59.512
Yay, art.

02:59.929 --> 03:01.138
They'll have an open bar.

03:01.138 --> 03:03.850
I won't go there
for that reason.

03:03.850 --> 03:07.645
Let's go invite Adam
and Jennifer to go with us.

03:07.645 --> 03:08.938
When's Adam movin' in?

03:08.938 --> 03:10.815
Honey, he moved in
a couple days ago.

03:10.815 --> 03:11.941
I told you...
you don't listen

03:11.941 --> 03:16.613
- to anything I say, do ya?
- I got a lot on my mind.

03:18.072 --> 03:22.076
Uh, what did Derek Jeter
bat last season?

03:22.076 --> 03:23.578
.309.

03:24.912 --> 03:27.081
It's important.

03:27.081 --> 03:27.790
Uh.

03:27.790 --> 03:29.667
We don't have
any couple friends.

03:29.667 --> 03:31.544
Jennifer's like
a little sister,

03:31.544 --> 03:32.795
and you like Adam, right?

03:32.795 --> 03:34.589
He's a good hang.

03:34.589 --> 03:36.424
So right there,
there's a couple

03:36.424 --> 03:38.926
in our building
that we don't hate.

03:38.926 --> 03:40.845
Yet.

03:40.845 --> 03:41.804
Honey, come on.

03:41.804 --> 03:43.180
They're just starting out.

03:43.180 --> 03:44.974
We need to set
a good example.

03:44.974 --> 03:47.602
- Okay, big guy?
- Fine.

03:47.602 --> 03:48.436
Thank you.

03:48.436 --> 03:50.855
Oh, hey, is this right?

03:50.855 --> 03:53.650
$85 for skin cream?

03:53.650 --> 03:56.694
Oh! This stuff is amazing.

03:56.694 --> 03:58.195
This is it.

03:58.821 --> 04:02.534
$85 for that tiny jar?

04:02.534 --> 04:05.453
What's in it, $80?

04:05.953 --> 04:10.207
Look, you spent $109
on a robot dog.

04:10.458 --> 04:13.795
There's no need to bring
Gizmo into this.

04:14.211 --> 04:17.173
He's programmed for love.

04:20.134 --> 04:21.803
You know what I'm gonna do?

04:21.803 --> 04:24.221
I'm gonna set up Russell
with my friend Karen.

04:24.221 --> 04:27.392
Why? What'd she do to you?

04:27.725 --> 04:29.936
I know he has
commitment issues,

04:29.936 --> 04:30.895
but he's not a bad guy.

04:30.895 --> 04:32.814
He just needs
the right woman to fix him.

04:32.814 --> 04:35.858
I think he needs the right
veterinarian to fix him,

04:35.858 --> 04:37.902
but go ahead, take a shot.

04:39.446 --> 04:40.613
What's this?

04:40.613 --> 04:41.406
What?

04:41.406 --> 04:43.991
Is this a wedding gift
registry?

04:43.991 --> 04:46.328
I mean, we just got engaged,
there's no wedding plans,

04:46.328 --> 04:49.372
and you're already
pickin' out gifts?

04:49.372 --> 04:50.540
I did it just for fun.

04:50.540 --> 04:51.749
I'm excited, aren't you?

04:51.749 --> 04:56.463
Mm, of course, just not
asparagus-steamer excited.

04:56.463 --> 04:58.423
Look, we're in no rush
to get married.

04:58.423 --> 05:00.467
Let's not worry
about it now, okay?

05:00.467 --> 05:02.927
- Okay.
- [KNOCKING]

05:05.388 --> 05:08.641
Oh, a cake plate.

05:08.641 --> 05:11.519
Cake is fun.

05:11.811 --> 05:13.521
- Hey, you!
- Hey, how are ya?

05:13.521 --> 05:16.691
Oh, Adam, we are so
excited you're engaged.

05:16.691 --> 05:17.525
You're living together!

05:17.525 --> 05:21.988
So you guys going Dutch
on the rent, or what?

05:23.573 --> 05:25.492
Anyway, we wanted
to know if you guys want

05:25.492 --> 05:27.744
to go with us to an art
opening on Saturday night.

05:27.744 --> 05:29.912
- Open bar.
- Sweet.

05:29.912 --> 05:32.164
Sounds fun.
What are you gonna wear?

05:32.164 --> 05:34.417
I'll probably buy
something new.

05:34.417 --> 05:35.167
Of course.

05:35.167 --> 05:37.420
I want you to take a look
at the new shoes I just bought.

05:37.420 --> 05:39.046
I'm wondering
if they're too slutty.

05:39.046 --> 05:40.715
- Are they clear?
- No.

05:40.715 --> 05:42.967
Then they're
not too slutty.

05:43.801 --> 05:47.304
Oh, well, you've got
a stain right there.

05:47.304 --> 05:48.390
Oh, come on!

05:48.390 --> 05:50.307
I got it from Audrey's
stupid bicycle.

05:50.307 --> 05:54.979
She's never used it.
It's been hanging in
our hallway for two years.

05:54.979 --> 05:56.898
Whoa, cool Mets stuff.

05:57.399 --> 05:58.775
Thanks. I wanna
hang it in here,

05:58.775 --> 06:01.027
but Jennifer wants me
to put it in my office.

06:01.027 --> 06:02.987
We'll figure out
a compromise, right?

06:02.987 --> 06:05.532
Oh, yeah, Audrey and I
compromise all the time,

06:05.532 --> 06:07.492
like when we got
our first apartment,

06:07.492 --> 06:08.451
she wanted
to get a cat.

06:08.451 --> 06:10.369
And I didn't want
to get a cat,

06:10.369 --> 06:14.206
so we compromised
and got a cat.

06:14.791 --> 06:16.834
[LAUGHING] That's too bad,

06:16.834 --> 06:18.628
but it's not
gonna happen to me.

06:18.628 --> 06:20.713
Jennifer's allergic to cats.

06:20.713 --> 06:22.924
So am I.

06:24.300 --> 06:26.761
Well, then, why'd you
let Audrey get her way?

06:26.761 --> 06:30.640
You have a biology textbook
around here?

06:30.807 --> 06:34.894
Look, we're gonna find
a place for all my stuff,

06:34.894 --> 06:37.063
and I'll get settled in.

06:37.063 --> 06:39.482
[SIGHING] You know,
I think marriage

06:39.482 --> 06:41.233
is gonna be really great.

06:41.233 --> 06:43.736
Based on what?

06:43.736 --> 06:45.237
Look.

06:45.237 --> 06:46.781
Look at this.

06:47.323 --> 06:50.159
Jennifer wants a cake plate
for our wedding.

06:50.159 --> 06:52.369
There is going to be cake.

06:52.369 --> 06:53.871
Yeah, sorry
to disappoint you,

06:53.871 --> 06:57.208
but there's not
gonna be any cake.

06:57.208 --> 06:59.043
What do you mean?

06:59.043 --> 07:00.169
Well, I mean...

07:00.169 --> 07:04.131
there's not gonna
be any cake.

07:04.131 --> 07:05.758
No, no, look.

07:05.758 --> 07:07.802
She signed up
for a cake plate,

07:07.802 --> 07:09.428
so there's got
to be cake.

07:09.428 --> 07:12.056
We have a cake plate,
12 years.

07:12.056 --> 07:13.891
No cake.

07:13.891 --> 07:15.309
How can that be?

07:15.309 --> 07:15.935
I don't know.

07:15.935 --> 07:17.562
We've also got a juicer,
no juice;

07:17.562 --> 07:20.982
a waffle maker, no waffles;
quesadilla maker...

07:20.982 --> 07:22.442
Uh, yeah, I like...

07:22.442 --> 07:23.735
No, señor.

07:24.527 --> 07:28.615
Well, that-- that
doesn't make any sense.

07:28.615 --> 07:30.700
I know. Welcome aboard.

07:31.408 --> 07:32.076
No, no, no, no, look!

07:32.076 --> 07:35.079
I don't wanna be trapped
in a cakeless marriage!

07:35.079 --> 07:37.540
Again, welcome aboard.

07:38.833 --> 07:41.127
There has to be cake.

07:41.127 --> 07:44.171
There will be cake.

07:44.171 --> 07:46.633
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

07:49.802 --> 07:50.928
Hey, hon.

07:50.928 --> 07:51.638
[CLOSES DOOR]

07:51.638 --> 07:53.180
What are you doin' now?

07:53.180 --> 07:54.932
Well, our place
is too cluttered,

07:54.932 --> 07:56.601
so I want to get rid
of some stuff.

07:56.601 --> 07:58.394
We can probably
sell this for money,

07:58.394 --> 08:03.107
buy yourself a thimble-full
of that face cream.

08:03.900 --> 08:05.860
My bicycle? No.

08:05.860 --> 08:06.736
Absolutely not.
Put it back.

08:06.736 --> 08:10.031
- You haven't used it
in two years.
- I'm gonna use it.

08:10.031 --> 08:11.824
You always say that,
but you never do.

08:11.824 --> 08:13.826
Jeff, if you
sell my bicycle,

08:13.826 --> 08:16.746
you will never see
me naked ever again.

08:16.746 --> 08:19.874
Oh, and the birthday deal?
That will be off.

08:19.874 --> 08:21.834
With or without you,

08:21.834 --> 08:25.630
the deal
will proceed forward.

08:26.631 --> 08:30.635
Okay, what
brought this on, huh?

08:30.635 --> 08:31.385
Well, Adam was telling me

08:31.385 --> 08:33.805
how Jennifer won't let him
hang his Mets thing up,

08:33.805 --> 08:36.182
- and dumb wedding gifts...
- Jeff, Jeff!

08:36.182 --> 08:37.517
I told you not
to be a bad example!

08:37.517 --> 08:39.686
Your bike's in the way.
I bump into it
all the time.

08:39.686 --> 08:42.313
Well, maybe if you
hadn't sold your bike
two years ago,

08:42.313 --> 08:45.191
we'd still be
riding together,
you'd be skinnier,

08:45.191 --> 08:47.359
and you wouldn't be
bumping into it.

08:47.359 --> 08:48.778
I get plenty of exercise.

08:48.778 --> 08:52.073
Last Saturday, I went
9 for 17 in softball.

08:52.073 --> 08:53.908
That's a lot of running.

08:53.908 --> 08:55.284
Yeah,
and how many beers

08:55.284 --> 08:57.369
did you have
after the game, huh?

08:57.369 --> 08:58.412
Nine or 17?

08:58.412 --> 09:01.123
I had maybe four...

09:01.123 --> 09:03.626
and then three lite ones...

09:03.626 --> 09:05.712
so five.

09:05.712 --> 09:09.173
What does any of this
have to do with your bicycle?

09:09.173 --> 09:11.217
Figure it out, Jeff.

09:11.217 --> 09:12.760
Give me a clue.

09:16.598 --> 09:19.559
Was that the clue?

09:22.019 --> 09:25.314
Hey. Grocery delivery boy
is here.

09:25.314 --> 09:31.362
Who am I, the lonely housewife
with no money to pay you?

09:31.362 --> 09:32.321
Mm, I like that game,

09:32.321 --> 09:34.866
but no, I actually
bought groceries.

09:34.866 --> 09:38.786
I got flour, sugar, eggs,
butter, vanilla,

09:38.786 --> 09:40.496
and this frosting
was on sale.

09:40.496 --> 09:44.541
Just gonna put it all
right by this mixing bowl.

09:47.461 --> 09:48.462
Are you gonna make a cake?

09:48.462 --> 09:51.674
No. No, I thought
you'd like to make it.

09:51.674 --> 09:53.175
Get a head start
on married life.

09:53.175 --> 09:55.344
I'm watching the game,
I'm drinking a beer...

09:55.344 --> 09:58.430
you're baking the cake,
the dog brings me my slippers.

09:58.430 --> 10:01.643
In your version of marriage,
am I allowed to vote?

10:01.643 --> 10:05.605
Yeah, honey, you can vote
while the cake is baking.

10:05.605 --> 10:08.274
Adam,
I don't really bake,

10:08.274 --> 10:09.901
and I haven't
planned on starting.

10:09.901 --> 10:12.444
Well then, why'd you
sign up for a cake plate

10:12.444 --> 10:13.946
on the wedding gift thing?

10:13.946 --> 10:16.323
I don't know, I just...

10:16.323 --> 10:17.784
What's going on?

10:17.784 --> 10:18.826
Well, honey,
things are

10:18.826 --> 10:20.119
happening pretty
quickly here,

10:20.119 --> 10:22.246
and I thought that I'd
have my same nice life,

10:22.246 --> 10:24.666
except you'd be in it,
which would make it better.

10:24.666 --> 10:25.792
But now I can't
put my Mets thing up,

10:25.792 --> 10:28.628
and I don't know
where my stuff's gonna go,

10:28.628 --> 10:29.837
and I don't want a cat.

10:29.837 --> 10:31.714
I'm allergic to cats.

10:31.714 --> 10:33.424
Yeah, so's Jeff.

10:33.424 --> 10:35.843
Adam, I don't know
what's happening here,

10:35.843 --> 10:38.680
but shouldn't you have
thought about all this

10:38.680 --> 10:39.263
before you proposed?

10:39.263 --> 10:42.224
I wasn't thinking
when I proposed.

10:42.224 --> 10:44.060
I just did it.

10:44.060 --> 10:46.478
Is that right?

10:46.478 --> 10:50.149
Well, you're obviously
thinking now.

10:50.149 --> 10:52.777
Are you sure
you wanna get married?

10:54.445 --> 10:56.113
Yes, I'm sure.

11:00.409 --> 11:02.244
Should I follow you?

11:02.244 --> 11:03.412
[DOOR SLAMS]

11:03.412 --> 11:05.247
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

11:08.417 --> 11:11.253
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

11:11.587 --> 11:13.255
So, what, you moved
to New York

11:13.255 --> 11:15.382
from Ohio to become
an actress?

11:15.382 --> 11:16.425
Uh-huh.

11:16.425 --> 11:17.551
Wow, that is a great plan.

11:17.551 --> 11:20.722
I'm surprised more girls
don't do that.

11:21.472 --> 11:22.598
You know,
you smell nice.

11:22.598 --> 11:25.142
And this shirt--
what is it, cotton or rayon?

11:25.142 --> 11:26.143
It's so soft.

11:26.143 --> 11:28.980
Oh, wait,
that's your skin.

11:29.939 --> 11:32.483
I should get back to work.

11:32.483 --> 11:34.110
Let's talk later.

11:34.110 --> 11:34.651
Oh, we will.

11:34.651 --> 11:37.864
I wanna hear
all about Ohio...

11:40.407 --> 11:42.201
You always have
to touch them.

11:42.201 --> 11:43.619
I'd be stupid not to.

11:43.619 --> 11:45.329
A touch says
"If you didn't think

11:45.329 --> 11:48.457
I wanted to have
sex with you, I do."

11:48.457 --> 11:51.127
You're here to meet
Jennifer's friend Karen,

11:51.127 --> 11:53.129
so why even touch
the ditzy waitress?

11:53.129 --> 11:53.963
Look, you're just jealous

11:53.963 --> 11:56.548
'cause your hitting-on-
ditzy-waitress days are over.

11:56.548 --> 12:01.053
They might not be.
Jennifer thinks I'm unsure
about getting married.

12:01.053 --> 12:03.097
Well, are you sure?

12:04.098 --> 12:04.640
Yeah, I am.

12:04.640 --> 12:08.394
- Ooh, ya paused.
- I know, I keep doing that.

12:08.394 --> 12:09.979
Oh, check it out.

12:14.483 --> 12:17.820
[LIKE CAVEMAN]
Mongo like art.

12:19.405 --> 12:22.784
Oh, here he comes.
I like Jeff. He's huge.

12:25.202 --> 12:27.538
Hey, Russell, I saw you
talking to that waitress.

12:27.538 --> 12:32.126
If anything happens there,
I'd appreciate some details.

12:32.126 --> 12:32.877
No problem. If you want,

12:32.877 --> 12:36.130
I'll set up a camera
and make you a tape.

12:37.131 --> 12:37.840
[GIGGLING]

12:37.840 --> 12:41.928
Yeah, it'd be funny
if he was kidding.

12:42.261 --> 12:44.263
Hey, you don't need
Russell's stories.

12:44.263 --> 12:46.808
I bet the love life
with Audrey's still good.

12:46.808 --> 12:48.725
Actually, we've
sort of wrapped up

12:48.725 --> 12:50.269
the sex portion
of the marriage.

12:50.269 --> 12:53.605
It's...been replaced
by Letterman.

12:55.232 --> 12:56.067
Ouch.

12:56.067 --> 12:58.735
How many times a week--
four, five?

12:58.735 --> 13:00.487
- Five.
- [APPROVES]

13:00.487 --> 13:03.532
You're talking about
Letterman, right?

13:08.037 --> 13:10.331
So, does Jeff at least get
why you're so upset

13:10.331 --> 13:11.707
about him wanting
to sell your bike yet?

13:11.707 --> 13:14.085
No, he doesn't get
that it's something

13:14.085 --> 13:14.961
we used to do together.

13:14.961 --> 13:16.295
I'm not gonna
explain it to him.

13:16.295 --> 13:18.965
He's gonna have
to figure it out himself.

13:24.720 --> 13:26.513
That may take a while.

13:28.307 --> 13:30.809
Adam, getting engaged
is the right decision.

13:30.809 --> 13:32.311
How long can you
prowl around bars,

13:32.311 --> 13:35.481
slinging pick-up lines
and havin' emotionless sex?

13:35.481 --> 13:37.942
I'll let you know.

13:39.776 --> 13:42.029
I'm just saying,
you wrestle enough bears,

13:42.029 --> 13:43.447
eventually you're
gonna get bitten.

13:43.447 --> 13:45.699
Yeah, I wrestled
a few bears in my day.

13:45.699 --> 13:49.370
Yeah. Wait, what
are bears, fat chicks?

13:50.997 --> 13:54.583
But the thing is, you know,
I had a lot of fun being single.

13:54.583 --> 13:55.792
I guess my question is

13:55.792 --> 13:57.628
how do you know
when you're done?

13:57.628 --> 13:59.964
Well, look, when you
find the right bear--

13:59.964 --> 14:00.797
What is it with bears?

14:00.797 --> 14:03.885
Were you raised by bears
or something?

14:04.385 --> 14:06.512
You know, guys,
as helpful as this is,

14:06.512 --> 14:08.222
I'm goin' to the bar.

14:08.222 --> 14:08.973
Good, good.

14:08.973 --> 14:11.808
You keep drinkin'
till you're happy.

14:11.934 --> 14:15.187
Actually, that's good advice.
I'll take it.

14:16.647 --> 14:21.235
So, have you figured out
why I'm so upset?

14:22.945 --> 14:25.489
I have some theories.

14:29.326 --> 14:31.578
How 'bout this urn, huh?

14:31.578 --> 14:34.540
It's blowin' me away.

14:40.337 --> 14:41.881
Hey, Russell.

14:42.464 --> 14:43.757
This is my friend Karen.

14:43.757 --> 14:45.009
Karen, Russell.

14:45.009 --> 14:46.218
Hey, nice to meet you.

14:46.218 --> 14:47.344
Nice to meet you.

14:47.344 --> 14:48.595
May I take your coat?

14:48.595 --> 14:50.932
Are you gonna
give it back?

14:50.932 --> 14:52.808
If it doesn't fit.

14:59.190 --> 15:00.857
Hi.

15:00.857 --> 15:01.650
Hi.

15:01.650 --> 15:02.776
I'm Sarah.

15:02.776 --> 15:03.819
I'm Adam.

15:03.819 --> 15:06.447
That's a really
nice jacket, Adam.

15:06.447 --> 15:07.823
Thanks.

15:09.033 --> 15:11.118
Oh.

15:12.661 --> 15:13.745
Hey.

15:13.745 --> 15:14.288
Oh, hey.

15:14.288 --> 15:15.539
Um, I saw you
talkin' to Audrey.

15:15.539 --> 15:18.709
She's still pretty made
about that bicycle thing,

15:18.709 --> 15:19.543
so you could help me out.

15:19.543 --> 15:22.338
Audrey wants you to figure
it out for yourself.

15:22.338 --> 15:24.173
Not gonna happen.

15:25.007 --> 15:25.716
That's hot.

15:25.716 --> 15:28.344
I didn't know nurses
had business cards.

15:28.344 --> 15:30.429
I started med school,
but took a break.

15:30.429 --> 15:33.015
My dream is to become
a pediatric surgeon.

15:33.015 --> 15:37.061
You dream of operating
on people's feet?

15:37.436 --> 15:39.521
No, that's a podiatrist.

15:39.521 --> 15:40.856
A pediatric surgeon--

15:40.856 --> 15:44.485
- Uh. Ah...
- Ah, you're joking.

15:44.485 --> 15:46.070
Are you ever serious?

15:46.070 --> 15:49.573
Tried it once.
Wasn't funny.

15:49.573 --> 15:50.616
Too bad.

15:50.616 --> 15:54.828
I think serious
can be very sexy.

15:56.247 --> 15:58.082
Seriously?

16:00.292 --> 16:02.419
And all my friends
were always telling me,

16:02.419 --> 16:05.797
"Sarah, the most interesting
things always happen to you.

16:05.797 --> 16:06.882
You should write a book."

16:06.882 --> 16:09.385
So, long story
short, ta-da!

16:09.385 --> 16:10.677
I'm writing it.
It's fiction.

16:10.677 --> 16:14.848
I've just changed the names
to protect the guilty.

16:15.682 --> 16:16.183
Good idea.

16:16.183 --> 16:18.227
It's sort of
Catcher in the Rye

16:18.227 --> 16:19.020
meets Sex in the City.

16:19.020 --> 16:21.272
I mean, I watch
that show, and I think,

16:21.272 --> 16:22.814
"I am so Carrie!"

16:22.814 --> 16:26.485
It's like her life
is my life is my life...

16:26.485 --> 16:28.862
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

16:34.743 --> 16:36.870
...is that there are
eight million people,

16:36.870 --> 16:38.289
but it's so hard

16:38.289 --> 16:40.374
to meet
the perfect person!

16:40.374 --> 16:42.793
Yeah, it is.

16:42.793 --> 16:44.211
Excuse me.

16:52.678 --> 16:54.763
This looks like
it symbolizes

16:54.763 --> 16:57.016
inner turmoil
and a sense of loss

16:57.016 --> 16:58.350
and confusion.

16:58.350 --> 16:59.768
What do you think?

17:00.227 --> 17:03.022
I think a monkey
got into the paint.

17:04.940 --> 17:06.608
Look, I'm sorry
I got so crazy.

17:06.608 --> 17:08.360
I guess I'm just
a little scared.

17:08.360 --> 17:10.279
Yeah, well,
I'm scared, too.

17:10.279 --> 17:11.613
Why are you scared?

17:11.613 --> 17:13.740
Because we did this
pretty quickly,

17:13.740 --> 17:16.910
and we don't seem
to be seeing things
the same way.

17:16.910 --> 17:19.746
We will, we will.
We just need time.

17:19.746 --> 17:21.332
Are you sure?

17:22.083 --> 17:23.417
Excuse me.

17:23.417 --> 17:25.169
What do you see
in this picture?

17:25.169 --> 17:29.673
I see a boat
on the Hudson River

17:29.673 --> 17:32.051
on a summer day.

17:32.051 --> 17:36.513
Yes, a boat
on the Hudson.

17:37.264 --> 17:38.390
Thanks.

17:38.390 --> 17:40.851
Yeah, we'll be fine.

17:43.104 --> 17:46.898
All you do is
repeat what I say.

17:47.233 --> 17:49.568
Have you had
an original thought

17:49.568 --> 17:51.445
in the last 40 years?

17:51.445 --> 17:55.782
And the hearing aid
goes off.

17:55.991 --> 17:59.995
Don't you walk away
from me, you son of a bitch!

18:04.791 --> 18:06.668
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

18:08.295 --> 18:10.381
Hey, take a look.

18:11.465 --> 18:12.383
A bicycle web site?

18:12.383 --> 18:14.718
Jeff, I told you,
you're not selling my bike.

18:14.718 --> 18:16.678
I know I'm not--
I'm getting one

18:16.678 --> 18:18.264
for myself,
so that we can ride

18:18.264 --> 18:21.475
through Central Park
together like we used to.

18:21.475 --> 18:24.895
- Really?
- Yeah.

18:25.937 --> 18:29.733
Uh, after softball.

18:30.192 --> 18:34.280
And not on Sunday
during football season.

18:43.955 --> 18:45.541
Ah, that was nice.

18:45.541 --> 18:47.751
You know, I'm glad I went.

18:47.751 --> 18:50.671
I'm glad you did, too.

18:50.671 --> 18:53.757
Hey, is it all right
if I sleep over?

18:54.591 --> 18:55.717
Here?

18:55.717 --> 18:56.718
Uh, sure.

18:56.718 --> 18:59.054
Great, because my apartment
is really tiny,

18:59.054 --> 19:00.514
and my roommate's
kind of a jerk.

19:00.514 --> 19:02.808
It's like she puts all
her food on one shelf

19:02.808 --> 19:04.476
of the fridge and tells
me not to touch it,

19:04.476 --> 19:06.562
and I'm like--
I'm gonna get some water--

19:06.562 --> 19:09.022
and I'm like, fine,
because I bring home

19:09.022 --> 19:11.650
really great food from
some of my catering jobs,

19:11.650 --> 19:12.818
and I don't let
her have any.

19:12.818 --> 19:15.196
It's not like I want
any of her food, anyway.

19:15.196 --> 19:17.239
I mean, she eats
all this organic stuff

19:17.239 --> 19:18.865
and last week she
became a vegan.

19:18.865 --> 19:20.116
I don't even know
what that is,

19:20.116 --> 19:22.619
because I grew up
in Cleveland
and we ate hotdogs.

19:22.619 --> 19:24.079
But I think she eats
some of my food, anyway,

19:24.079 --> 19:26.832
because last week I brought
all these giant shrimp home,

19:26.832 --> 19:29.335
and I counted 'em
before I put 'em in the fridge,

19:29.335 --> 19:32.171
and the next day,
two were gone.

19:32.171 --> 19:36.300
Wait, did you just drink water
and never stop talking?

19:37.426 --> 19:40.262
Oh, yeah, I guess I did.

19:40.262 --> 19:41.888
You wanna do it again?

19:45.851 --> 19:48.520
Yes, I do.

19:52.608 --> 19:53.400
Wow.

19:53.400 --> 19:55.361
I just kept going,
didn't I?

19:55.361 --> 19:57.613
Thank you, open bar!

19:59.948 --> 20:03.327
Hey, you wanna
do it again?

20:04.620 --> 20:06.497
[SNORTS]

20:07.664 --> 20:08.832
Again.

20:08.832 --> 20:11.126
Remember that?

20:13.920 --> 20:16.257
Oh, yeah,
that's so good.

20:16.257 --> 20:18.049
Oh, let me
just lick that.

20:18.049 --> 20:20.051
There you go.

20:20.051 --> 20:21.094
Mmm.

20:21.094 --> 20:22.263
Delicious cake.

20:22.263 --> 20:23.430
[LAUGHING]

20:23.430 --> 20:26.182
Now that we're done
with the cake,

20:26.182 --> 20:29.060
we can have dessert.

20:29.353 --> 20:32.231
Actually,
I'm really tired.

20:32.231 --> 20:33.815
Okay if we wait
till tomorrow?

20:33.815 --> 20:37.736
It already is tomorrow
under these sheets.

20:37.944 --> 20:40.572
Come on, I'll make it
worth your while.

20:40.572 --> 20:41.907
All right, fine.

20:41.907 --> 20:45.076
We have the rest
of our lives to do this.

20:46.328 --> 20:48.997
I think we're gonna
be really happy.

20:48.997 --> 20:50.541
Me too.

20:51.542 --> 20:52.584
Here.

20:52.584 --> 20:54.670
You can watch
Letterman.

20:54.670 --> 20:59.007
[BAND PLAYS]

21:00.509 --> 21:01.885
Letterman?

21:01.885 --> 21:05.138
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]
